**Design Inspiration & UX Research

To inform the visual design and layout decisions for the project, several existing websites were analysed. These references helped identify design patterns, structures, and layout approaches that could be adapted for the redesigned website.
The research focused on visual hierarchy, navigation structure, content organisation, and case study presentation, ensuring the final design would be both visually engaging and user-friendly.

**Visual Design Inspiration
Gym Fitness Landing Page

GYM Fitness Landing Page Design By Lathiya Solutions
View Here: https://www.behance.net/gallery/177620101/GYM-Fitness-Landing-Page-Design-By-Lathiya-Solutions

This landing page was analysed to better understand visual styling and layout patterns commonly used in gym and fitness-related websites.

**Design Features

- High-impact imagery that immediately communicates the theme
- Clear section structure for services, membership, and facilities
- Bold typography used to highlight key messaging
- Effective use of contrast to separate content sections

**Key UX Insights

- Use large hero imagery to immediately communicate the brand and environment
- Structure content into clear sections such as classes, membership, and facilities
- Maintain strong visual hierarchy to guide user attention
- Use consistent typography and spacing to improve readability

**Hero Section Inspiration
MetaDesign

View Here: https://metadesign.com/en/

The MetaDesign homepage was used as inspiration for the hero banner interaction and layout structure.

**Design Features
- Split layout with content distributed across the left and right side
- Smooth horizontal movement creating an engaging visualal landing page
- Minimalist typography allowing the hero visuals to stand out
- Balanced layout that keeps the interface clean and focused

**Key UX Insights

- Introduce motion for the hero banner to create engagemen
- Maintain a balanced layout between text and imagery
- Use animation minimally to enhance the experience without distracting users

These elements influenced the interactive hero section concept for the redesigned homepage.

**Layout & UX Structure Research
Garland PowerSports

Garland PowerSports
View Here: https://www.garlandpowersports.com/

This website was analysed to understand how vehicle-related products and services are structured within a commercial website layout.

**Design Features

- Focused theme navigation structur
- Clear categorisation of services
- Strong use of imagery to showcase products
- Structured content hierarchy supporting quick browsing

**Key UX Insights

- Organise content into clear product categories
- Use strong imagery to support product discovery
- Ensure navigation allows users to quickly locate relevant information

These insights informed the UX workflow for presenting bike-related content and services within the design.

**Case Study Layout Research
Vicky March

View Here: https://www.vickymarch.com/work/studystream

This case study was analysed to understand how UX projects can be clearly documented and presented within a portfolio.

**Design Features

- Clear storytelling structure for the design process
- Logical progression from problem → research → solution
- Clean layout that separates each section of the case study
- Balanced use of visuals and text

**Key UX Insights

- Present UX work as a narrative showing the full design process
- Break down sections into research, ideation, design, and results
- Maintain visual clarity through spacing and section separation

These insights influenced the structure of the project case study within the portfolio.

